1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 Random Variable (RV)

A random variable is a function that assigns a real number to each outcome in the sample space.

Two types:

1️⃣ Discrete Random Variable
2️⃣ Continuous Random Variable

🔹 Discrete Random Variable

Takes countable values.

Example:
Number of heads in 3 coin tosses.

